cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper deals with the use of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) for generating synthetic data and using it for training deep Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of reinforcement learning (RL) for selecting meaningful synthetic examples, which falls under the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves the use of GANs, which is a popular topic in the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of discriminator's realism confidence score and the confidence on the target label of the synthetic data, which falls under the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its method on two challenging face attribute classification datasets, which falls under the sub-category cs.GR (Graphics).
